
 vsleep - Wrapper function of sleep(Standard C Library)

 What is it?
 -----------

 The vsleep is a wrapper function of sleep(Standard C Library).
 This function count down second of sleep remain and no characters
 at finish function.

 How to Compile
 --------------
 Use makefile or compile manually. 

 How To Use
 ----------
 See sample source code(sample.c).

 Files
 -----
 vsleep.c : function body.
 vsleep.h : header file, include your program.
 sample.c : sample source of how to use vsleep().
 makefile : makefile(GNU Make 3.81)

 Test Environment
 ----------------
  o Mac OS X(10.5.8/Leopard)
    - gcc version 4.0.1 (Apple Inc. build 5493).
